      <p>
        <a href="http://elephantsandbees.com/">The Elephants and Bees Project</a> is a collaberative effort between <a href="#sec5">Save The Elephants</a> (also a Karma Grove charity), Disney's Animal Kingdom and the world-renownded Oxford University. The partnership aims to protect African Elephants in rural areas through an innovative study that seeks an in-depth understanding of elephant behaviour. Ultimately, the products of this innovative research and its on-the-ground implementation reduce damage from crop-raiding elephants and the killing of these magnificent animals as a result.</p>

        <p>Elephants and Bees uses African Elephants' instinctive avoidance of honey bees to accomplish the complex problem of reducing crop destruction while protecting elephants from violence. To do so in an environmentally-conscious way, the project's members are exploring the use of novel Beehive fences--an invention of Dr. Lucy King. These fences are designed to be a natural elephant deterrent, and they offer the additional benefits of creating a social and economic boost to poverty-stricken rural communities via pollination services and the sustainable harvesting of “Elephant-Friendly Honey”. To learn more about The Elephants and Bees Project, please visit their website <a href="www.elephantsandbees.org">www.ElephantsAndBees.org</a>.
      </p>

      <p>
        Karma Grove founder Joshua Montross proudly signed a check for $50 in September, 2014 and donated it to The Elephants and Bees project. The funds donated were raised from your purchases through Karma Grove. Thank you for your gifts!
